As a learner, you do the following:
- determine your own project, your own goal, your own path of learning;
- for every project, idea, goal, set up a dedicated blog site;
- for each of your ideas, projects, goals, keep working on them;
- while you are working on your projects and ideas and goals, faculties will examine them and give advice;
- there is no term, no deadline, no fee, no admin, no exam; you can be here learning for life;
- you should take a look what other learners are doing, that is a great way to learn;
- if you see anything you like from other sources, you can copy them and make them become your owns and further develop; there is no copyright about ideas;

once you have your project site created, you can register it here, so others can visit:
http://127.0.0.1:43110/12UZW9MXSJEAMRrPvm79smMbFr7kgN4R1x/

This question we need to ask again and again. And for the time being, let's put some of his traits here:

- it is not a common college; here, student the learner dictates everything; not admission officers because therre is none of that type; not admins because there is none; not professors, they are here to advise and advise only;
- it is not a common college, where most students are not sure what they are learning are of any practical use; 
- it is not a common college, where budget always plays a bigger role than students' and faculties' interest;
- it is not a common college, where exams are the final evaluations;
- it is not a common college, where political right or wrong has to be somewhat observed; not here; right or wrong, you say it; 
- it is not a common college, where faculties serve students but in reality they are higher in hierarchy; here in College 34, every one is truly equal; just take a look of their ids, they are equal in everyway;
- it is not a common college; here, the tuition is free;
- it is not a common college; here, you decide the curriculum, the term, the time to finish or study for life if you want;

Good things are easy to recognize. so we do not need to worry about them.

Certains things are ok, even if it may vary widely in taste, for example if someone curses, say things like fuk this and fuk that, that probably is ok depending on the situation, guys do that all the time in life anyway.

But there are bad things. What are bad things, these are bad things:

- illegal activities; 
- extremely offensive languages and acts; 
- things too selfish and neglect of others' interest;

Let's do not do bad things.

- certain cursing words should be avoided;
- be respectful to others;
- try to be helpful;
- try to contribute to the community;

when thinking the design of a learning platform, we are concerned about the following:

- how easy is it to use;
- how long it could last? could it pass from generation to generation?
- what kind of tools are availalbe;
- how many people it can engage?
- is it secure and safe?

on all of these issues, zero34 platform is possitive:

- it is easy to use;
- it easily lasts forever, it is free, depends only on your own computer and its connetion to the info highway;
- blog, forum are the basic tools now, but we can expect it grows to comtain many more;
- it can infinitely scale up;
- it is secure;

- it is fast, reliable.

because it is located on your own computer, it is fast, reliable; many of us have been using this system and writing over thousands of articles, it has never failed a single time; and it is always fast;

comparing to some other system of tradition online systems they are not reliable, some times is ok, often glichy, slow, cannot work properly;

- it is secure, it is yours, and even if your computer fails, your contents are still very safe, because they are stored not just on your computer but also on your peers computers; you can access them easily from any where and on any computer;
- it is infinitely scalable; 

- and it is free;

do whatever you want. or simply do nothing.

some things you could think of doing are:

- write and let others hear you
- pick up a project and work on it, there are so many projects you can design and do;
- hang around here, look around, and make some recommendations;
- or very likley, you are a guru of something; so you should consider teach, help others grow; men  instinctively want to disseminate their genes, so please, also disseminate your knowledge and ideas, they conceive and grow too;

easy 123.

first, create a blog; that is your homepage;
second, let us know you and your homepage; so we know what is relevant and important for you;
third, start learning, thinking, creating, building up something interesting and useful for others;

cheers,
your team at 34

sure this is a freeland. you do whatever you think that is sensible and fair, as long as you abide by the laws.

here are a few tips that we think you might consider:

- because it is so easy to build up blog sites on 34, you can easily manage many different sites for various purposes. you could choose to be yourself like in your real world life; or you could choose to expose your other personalities and develop them to your advantage;
- in real world it is hard; it is hard to complain, because really other people do not want to hear complaints, we all want to live a easy and simple life; so, you can complain here. complain is a good thing, it channels away your anger, it let others know there is an opportunity, and in some cases, it entertains others; so complain it loud here;
- in real world it is hard; it is hard because we all have to pretend to be smart; here, please, it does not matter. most of us are foolish, that is a fact. so let's remain to be foolish here. by accepting our own foolishness, we can relax, and that is the most effective state to truly learn;

you can very conveniently use your blog sites (you can easily clone and build as many sties as you like) for the following purposes - 
- set a goal and work toward that goal, use your site as the notebook, keep accumulating materials and thoughts, while others can make suggestions;
- write down your thoughts, like a diary; a few years later these thoughts will look very interesting, and helpful, in helping you grow and set new life goals;
- use this as a communication platform to inform and engage with others; you will be supprised how many people pay attention to you and your thoughts; 
- this is by far the safest place to place your words, all of your words sit on your own desktop, but at the same time viewable by the whole world. so you have the whole world witnessing who you are and what you think. that is very assuring, if you are a nice guy.

- trial and error, do not worry about errors or mistakes, if something goes wrong permanetnly, then delete it and create new site, it is so easy to create on 34;
- talk to others; 34ers are mostly nice people; they went through the same problems and they are happy to guide and share;
- College34 itself remains under heavy lifting and development; what we have achieved yes is quite amazing but even bigger things are down the road; so allow it room to try out and grow, fix things wrong youself if you can, and it is common many 34ers have their own projects going on right now.

enjoy. try something new.

yours,
co34er

